<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-20T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="547" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1065: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-20T11:00:00-07:00">April 20, 1931—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:25 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>29. Minister of Foreign Affairs has informed me that the Jefe Politico of
                            Puerto Barrios yesterday arrested General Filiberto Diaz Zelaya and four
                            companions who were on their way to join the Honduran revolution. All
                            five are now locked up here.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Tegucigalpa.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>